            <div type="translation" resp="part:reda part:emfr">
                
                <p n="1">Prosperity! Fortune!</p>
                <p n="1">Second year of the glorious king Kulottuṅga Cōḻa, emperor of the three worlds.</p>
                <p n="1">This is the manner in which <gap reason="lost"/>, Lord of Puttūr, who resides in Pērakaḻi in the <gap reason="lost"/>kūṟṟam <gap reason="lost"/> gave a <foreign>devadāna</foreign>.</p>
                <p n="1-2">In this Pērakaḻi, which comes as a property <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kāṇi</foreign></supplied> owned by our father,
                    after having made the installation of a <foreign>liṅga</foreign> of Śiva,
                    having built a glorious stone-temple ...,
                    having installed some images such as Viṉāyaka and Kṣetrapāla,
                    having installed glorious images of the Nāyaṉmārs,
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">he gave</supplied> as <foreign>devadāna</foreign>
                    <gap reason="ellipsis"/>
                    a quarter <foreign>cey</foreign> of land in the west of this village and a quarter a quarter <foreign>cey</foreign> of land in the east as per this <supplied reason="subaudible">measuring</supplied> rod.
                    
                </p>
                
            </div>
            
